@page
@model IndexModel
@{
    ViewData["Title"] = "Home page";
}

<div class="text-center">
    <h1 class="display-4">Welcome</h1>
    <h3>This template uses ASP.NET Core Razor Pages Framework.</h3>
    <p>Also It uses the default bootstrap framework for UI. </p>
    <p>Learn about <a href="https://docs.microsoft.com/aspnet/core">building Web apps with ASP.NET Core</a>.</p>


    <h4>The template is created using ASP.NET Core Razor pages web template with individual user authentication</h4>
</div>

<div class="bd-example mt-lg-5">
    <div id="carouselExampleCaptions" class="carousel slide" data-ride="carousel">
        <ol class="carousel-indicators">
            <li data-target="#carouselExampleCaptions" data-slide-to="0" class="active"></li>
            <li data-target="#carouselExampleCaptions" data-slide-to="1"></li>
            <li data-target="#carouselExampleCaptions" data-slide-to="2"></li>
        </ol>
        <div class="carousel-inner">
            <div class="carousel-item active">
                <img src="~/images/banner1.svg" alt="ASP.NET" class="d-block w-100">
                <div class="carousel-caption d-none d-md-block">
                    <h5> Learn how to build ASP.NET apps that can run anywhere.</h5>
                    <p>
                        <a class="btn btn-primary text-light" href="https://go.microsoft.com/fwlink/?LinkID=525028&clcid=0x409">
                            Learn More..
                        </a>
                    </p>
                </div>
            </div>
            <div class="carousel-item">
                <img src="~/images/banner2.svg" alt="ASP.NET" class="d-block w-100">
                <div class="carousel-caption d-none d-md-block">
                    <h5> There are powerful new features in Visual Studio for building modern web apps.</h5>
                    <p>
                        <a class="btn btn-primary text-light" href="https://go.microsoft.com/fwlink/?LinkID=525030&clcid=0x409">
                            Learn More..
                        </a>
                    </p>
                </div>
            </div>
            <div class="carousel-item">
                <img src="~/images/banner3.svg" alt="ASP.NET" class="d-block w-100">
                <div class="carousel-caption d-none d-md-block">
                    <h5> Learn how Microsoft's Azure cloud platform allows you to build, deploy, and scale web apps.</h5>
                    <a class="btn btn-primary text-light" href="https://go.microsoft.com/fwlink/?LinkID=525030&clcid=0x409">
                        Learn More..
                    </a>
                </div>
            </div>
        </div>
        <a class="carousel-control-prev" href="#carouselExampleCaptions" role="button" data-slide="prev">
            <span class="carousel-control-prev-icon" aria-hidden="true"></span>
            <span class="sr-only">Previous</span>
        </a>
        <a class="carousel-control-next" href="#carouselExampleCaptions" role="button" data-slide="next">
            <span class="carousel-control-next-icon" aria-hidden="true"></span>
            <span class="sr-only">Next</span>
        </a>
    </div>
</div>


<div class="card text-center mt-lg-5">
    <div class="card-header">
        <h1>Additional Features included in this template: </h1>
    </div>

</div>

<div class="card-deck mt-xl-5">
    <div class="card">
        <div class="card-body">
            <h4 class="card-title">Scroll to top Button</h4>
            <p class="card-text">Added necessary code to show up scroll to top button at the bottom left corner of the page.</p>

            <a href="#" class="btn btn-dark btn-lg " role="button"><i class="fas fa-arrow-alt-circle-up"></i></a>
        </div>
    </div>
    <div class="card">
        <div class="card-body">
            <h4 class="card-title">Sticky Navigation Bar</h4>
            <p class="card-text">The navigation bar is visible always at the top of the page.</p>
            <p class="card-text"><small class="text-muted">Note: this is not an additional feature, just a modification to the existing Navbar</small></p>
        </div>
    </div>

</div>

<div class="card-deck mt-xl-5">
    <div class="card">
        <div class="card-body">
            <h4 class="card-title">Use System Variables</h4>
            <p class="card-text">
                Shows how to use system variables in the Razor pages. The demonstration can be found in the
                <a class="btn btn-primary text-light" asp-area="" asp-page="/About">About</a> page.
            </p>


        </div>
    </div>
    <div class="card">
        <div class="card-body">
            <h5 class="card-title">Bootstrap Carousel</h5>
            <p class="card-text">
                Bootstrap carousel was available with the previously ASP.NET core 2.1 template. So I have added it here with modified bootstrap
                code to match the version use in this template.
            </p>
            <p class="card-text"><small class="text-muted"></small></p>
        </div>
    </div>

</div>

<div class="card text-center mt-lg-5">
    <div class="card-header">
        <h2>And more features to come .. </h2>
    </div>

</div>

<h1 class="display-1">How to use this template:</h1>

<div class="card text-center">
    <div class="card-body">
        <p class="card-text">Fork or create a branch or download the code to your computer and open using any version of Visual Studio 2017. I used Visual Studio 2017 Community edition. </p>
        <p class="card-text">Then to suit your requirement, change the namespaces in the entire solution using "Find and replace" (Ctrl +H).</p>
        <p class="card-text">You may also need to change the http, and https port numbers for the project. You can change it directly in the "lanchSetting.json" file.</p>
    </div>

</div>
<div class="card text-center mt-lg-5">
    <div class="card-body">
        <p class="card-text">I will add more tempaltes later.</p>
        <p class="card-text">And also Visual Studio 2019, 2022 templates will be added. Stay tuned..</p>
    </div>

</div>

<environment include="Development,Staging">
    <div class="card text-center mt-xl-5">
        <div class="card-header">
            <h1>Visual Studio Solution Name: <span class="text-success">@Html.DisplayFor(model => model.SolutionName)</span></h1>
        </div>
        <div class="card-body">
            <h3 class="card-title">Project Name : <span class="span-bold text-danger">@Html.DisplayFor(model => model.MyApplicationName)</span></h3>
            <p class="card-text"> ASPNETCORE_ENVIRONMENT : <span class="btn btn-danger">@Html.DisplayFor(model => model.ThisEnvironment)</span> </p>

            <p>Application Name : <span class="btn alert-primary">@Html.DisplayFor(model => model.MyApplicationName)</span> </p>
            <p>Current RunTime Version : <span class="btn alert-primary">@Html.DisplayFor(model => model.CurrentRunTimeVersion)</span> </p>
        </div>
        <div class="card-footer text-muted">
            <p><span class="btn alert-primary">@Html.DisplayFor(model => model.version)</span> </p>
        </div>
    </div>

</environment>





